
[1]tattoo

   TATTOO', n. [Eng. tap.] A beat of drum at night, giving notice to
   soldiers to retreat, or to repair to their quarters in garrison, or to
   their tents in camp.

   TATTOO', v.t. [In the South Sea isles.] To prick the skin, and stain
   the punctured spots with a black substance, forming lines and figures
   upon the body. In some isles, the inhabitants tattoo the face, in
   others only the body. The same practice exists among other rude
   nations.

   TATTOO', n. Figures on the body made by punctures and stains in lines
   and figures.
